+
+The platform-specific manifest digest, not the mutable tag and not only the
+multi-platform index digest, is the runtime identity. The human-readable tag is
+retained before `@sha256` so package/image version drift is visible in review.
+
+## Required PW-I01 Paths
+
+PW-I01 MUST use these exact paths:
+
+```text
+tests/playwright/
+├── package.json
+├── package-lock.json
+├── playwright.config.ts
+├── README.md
+└── runner/
+    ├── bootstrap.spec.ts
+    ├── run.sh
+    └── validate-lock.mjs
+
+tests/test_playwright_bootstrap.py
+```
+
+PW-I01 may add only the root `.gitignore` entries needed for:
+
+```text
+/test-results/playwright/
+/tests/playwright/node_modules/
+```
+
+CI registration remains manifest-first through the existing files named in
+PW-I01. Generated CI artifacts MUST NOT be edited by hand.
+
+## Node Project Contract
+
+`tests/playwright/package.json` MUST declare:
+
+- `private: true`;
+- `type: "module"`;
+- `packageManager: "npm@11.13.0"`;
+- exact engines `node: "24.17.0"` and `npm: "11.13.0"`;
+- exact dev dependency `@playwright/test: "1.61.1"` with no range prefix;
+- exact script `test:platform: "playwright test --config=playwright.config.ts
+  --project=chromium"`.
+
+The lock file MUST:
+
+- be generated with npm `11.13.0`;
+- use lockfile version 3;
+- contain no floating dependency declaration;
+- contain only `https://registry.npmjs.org/` remote `resolved` URLs, with no
+  alternate host, HTTP, Git, file, or credential-bearing URL;
+- contain an npm integrity value for every remotely resolved package;
+- be installed with `npm ci`, never `npm install`, during runner execution.
+
+`tests/playwright/runner/validate-lock.mjs` MUST fail closed unless all lockfile
+rules above and the exact root `@playwright/test: "1.61.1"` declaration hold.
+The dependency phase MUST run this validator before `npm ci` on every
+invocation; CI-only validation is insufficient.
+
+PW-I01 MUST include `runner/bootstrap.spec.ts` so its required platform target
+has one test from the first commit. This test MUST load the Playwright project
+without requesting `browser`, `context`, or `page`; PW-I02 owns the first
+Chromium launch and isolation test. The bootstrap test remains part of later
+platform runs. `--pass-with-no-tests` is forbidden because a missing suite must
+never become a successful run.
+
+No separate `typescript` package is selected. Playwright's supported built-in
+TypeScript loading is sufficient for the initial configuration and tests.
+
+## Playwright Configuration Contract
+
+`tests/playwright/playwright.config.ts` MUST initially define exactly one
+browser project named `chromium` using Playwright's bundled Chromium. Test
+discovery MUST use project-relative `testDir: "."`, include
+`runner/bootstrap.spec.ts`, `platform/**/*.spec.ts`, and
+`services/**/*.spec.ts`, and exclude `node_modules` and the result root. It MUST
+set `retries: 0`, read the output directory from the required
+`PLAYWRIGHT_RESULTS_DIR` environment variable, fail when that variable is
+absent, and set `chromiumSandbox: false` explicitly. PW-I01 runs only controlled
+local content with no network and does not introduce the additional seccomp
+artifact required for a sandboxed `pwuser` configuration.
+
+PW-I01 MUST NOT enable Firefox, WebKit, videos, service-specific URLs,
+authentication, retries, or live Homelab tests. Later tickets own those
+concerns.
+
+The initial output root is `/results` inside the container and
+`$REPOSITORY_ROOT/test-results/playwright` on the host.
+
+## Runner Entry Contract
+
+`tests/playwright/runner/run.sh` is the only Docker invocation authority for
+local and CI execution. Make and Gitea Actions call the wrapper; they MUST NOT
+duplicate `docker run` arguments.
+
+The wrapper MUST:
+
+1. Resolve the repository root from its own path, not the caller's current
+   directory.
+2. Create the host results directory before starting Docker.
+3. invoke the exact image and `--platform linux/amd64`;
+4. use `docker run --rm --init` for dependency installation and
+   `docker run --rm --init --shm-size=1g` for test execution; sharing the host
+   IPC namespace is forbidden;
+5. mount the repository read-only at `/workspace`;
+6. mount the results directory read-write at `/results`;
+7. set the working directory to `/workspace/tests/playwright`;
+8. create one uniquely named temporary Docker volume for
+   `/workspace/tests/playwright/node_modules` and remove it in an exit trap;
+9. run a dependency phase with that volume read-write, explicit Docker bridge
+   networking, no secrets, and only directory setup, version checks, lockfile
+   validation, and the locked npm install command;
+10. run the test phase with `--network none` and the dependency volume
+    read-only;
+11. provide one ephemeral writable `/tmp` tmpfs with mode `1777` in each phase,
+    set `HOME=/tmp/pw-home`, and set `npm_config_cache=/tmp/npm-cache`;
+12. run both phases with a read-only root filesystem, all Linux capabilities
+    dropped, and `no-new-privileges`;
+13. validate the lockfile and then install the locked project with
+    `npm ci --ignore-scripts --no-audit --no-fund`;
+14. run only the selected package script with no network-fetched executable;
+15. preserve the child exit code unchanged until PW-I03 introduces the final
+    `0/1/2` result mapper;
+16. reject invoking UID `0` or GID `0` before creating a volume or container,
+    then run the test phase as the invoking non-root host UID/GID so `/results`
+    ownership is correct without `chown` or an added capability;
+17. never mount the Docker socket, home directory, credential directory, SSH
+    directory, or any service runtime path;
+18. pass only the environment variables shown below; host environment forwarding,
+    `--env-file`, and secret injection are forbidden in PW-I01.
+
+The dependency phase has registry access but no credentials, service variables,
+results mount, or browser execution:
+
+```bash
+docker run --rm --init \
+  --platform linux/amd64 \
+  --network bridge \
+  --read-only \
+  --cap-drop ALL \
+  --security-opt no-new-privileges \
+  --tmpfs /tmp:rw,nosuid,nodev,size=512m,mode=1777 \
+  --workdir /workspace/tests/playwright \
+  --mount type=bind,src="$REPOSITORY_ROOT",dst=/workspace,readonly \
+  --mount type=volume,src="$NODE_MODULES_VOLUME",dst=/workspace/tests/playwright/node_modules \
+  --env CI=true \
+  --env HOME=/tmp/pw-home \
+  --env npm_config_cache=/tmp/npm-cache \
+  --env npm_config_registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/ \
+  mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.61.1-noble@sha256:cf0daee9b994042e011bc29f20cdff1a9f682a039b43fcd738f7d8a9d3bcd9d6 \
+  /bin/bash -lc 'mkdir -p "$HOME" "$npm_config_cache" && test "$(node --version)" = v24.17.0 && test "$(npm --version)" = 11.13.0 && node runner/validate-lock.mjs && npm ci --ignore-scripts --no-audit --no-fund'
+```
+
+The test phase has no network, a private shared-memory mount, and cannot modify
+installed dependencies:
+
+```bash
+docker run --rm --init --shm-size=1g \
+  --platform linux/amd64 \
+  --network none \
+  --read-only \
+  --cap-drop ALL \
+  --security-opt no-new-privileges \
+  --user "$HOST_UID:$HOST_GID" \
+  --tmpfs /tmp:rw,nosuid,nodev,size=512m,mode=1777 \
+  --workdir /workspace/tests/playwright \
+  --mount type=bind,src="$REPOSITORY_ROOT",dst=/workspace,readonly \
+  --mount type=volume,src="$NODE_MODULES_VOLUME",dst=/workspace/tests/playwright/node_modules,readonly \
+  --mount type=bind,src="$RESULTS_DIR",dst=/results \
+  --env CI=true \
+  --env HOME=/tmp/pw-home \
+  --env npm_config_cache=/tmp/npm-cache \
+  --env PLAYWRIGHT_RESULTS_DIR=/results \
+  mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.61.1-noble@sha256:cf0daee9b994042e011bc29f20cdff1a9f682a039b43fcd738f7d8a9d3bcd9d6 \
+  /bin/bash -lc 'mkdir -p "$HOME" "$npm_config_cache" && npm run test:platform'
+```
+
+The shell fragments are contract templates, not implementation in this decision
+artifact. They are the complete network, privilege, environment, mount, and
+runtime-identity contract; PW-I01 MUST NOT add or remove an argument in those
+categories. PW-I01 owns only safe array-based shell construction, variable
+names, diagnostics, invoking UID/GID capture, collision-safe volume naming, and
+trap syntax. Those mechanics MUST NOT alter the observable Docker arguments,
+exit code, or lifecycle. The dependency volume MUST be removed after every
+pass, failure, signal, or prerequisite error.
+
+## Network Boundary
+
+PW-I01 platform tests MUST run with `--network none`; they use only controlled
+local content. This makes test execution independent of DNS, TLS, Keycloak,
+services, and the Internet.
+
+The preceding dependency phase uses Docker's default bridge and therefore has
+general outbound network capability; Docker bridge networking is not a
+destination allowlist. The exposure is bounded by receiving no runtime secret,
+host environment, service variable, results mount, or browser execution;
+disabling package lifecycle scripts; and validating before installation that
+every remote lockfile URL uses `https://registry.npmjs.org/` with an integrity
+value. A future requirement for network-enforced destination filtering needs a
+separate reviewed proxy or egress-control decision and MUST NOT be claimed by
+PW-I01.
+
+Service-network mode is not enabled by PW-I01. A later reviewed ticket MUST
+explicitly introduce its network argument and service/Keycloak target contract
+before a live service suite runs. Host networking, published ports, and Docker
+socket access remain forbidden.
+
+The dependency phase runs as image root but launches no browser and receives no
+secret. The test phase runs as the invoking non-root host UID/GID with
+Chromium's sandbox explicitly disabled. This decision compensates with
+controlled local content, network-none platform mode, private shared memory, an
+ephemeral container, read-only root/source/dependency mounts, writable state
+limited to tmpfs and `/results`, dropped capabilities, no-new-privileges, no
+Docker socket, and no persistent browser state. Untrusted websites are outside
+the platform scope.
+
+PW-I01 introduces no secret interface. A later reviewed identity/service ticket
+MUST define an explicit environment-variable allowlist before credentials can
+be injected at container start; it may not introduce an env file, host
+environment forwarding, credential mount, or image-baked value.
+
+## Local And CI Invocation
+
+Local operators and CI MUST use the same command from the repository root:
+
+```bash
+make test-playwright-platform
+```
+
+The generated Make target MUST invoke:
+
+```bash
+bash tests/playwright/runner/run.sh platform
+```
+
+No global Node.js, npm, Playwright, browser, or browser-system package is a host
+prerequisite. Beyond the repository-standard Make, Bash, Python, and Git
+validation toolchain, Docker access, the pinned MCR image, and dependency-phase
+access to `https://registry.npmjs.org/` are the only runner-specific host
+prerequisites.
+
+## Version And Upgrade Contract
+
+An upgrade MUST change every affected item below in one reviewed PR:
+
+1. This decision's release, tag, index digest, selected manifest digest,
+   Node/npm, browser, package-integrity, and layer evidence.
+2. `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, runner image reference, runtime version
+   assertions, lock validator, Playwright configuration, and bootstrap contract
+   tests wherever the changed values appear.
+3. Manifest-first CI source and generated outputs if their commands or pinned
+   values are affected.
+4. Platform self-test evidence and all active service smoke evidence.
+
+The upgrade author MUST verify the tag and digests from MCR and the package
+version and integrity from the official NPM registry. The author MUST also
+verify the selected manifest's Node/npm and browser values, regenerate the lock
+file with the selected npm, run the lock validator, and verify that the current
+accepted image digest remains available before merge. A tag-only, partial, or
+evidence-free update is invalid.
+
+Rollback is one Git revert of the complete upgrade PR to the previous accepted
+decision/package/configuration/runner/test/CI set. Image, package, browser,
+Node/npm assertions, lock file, validator expectations, and generated CI MUST
+roll back together. The reverted platform self-test MUST pass against the prior
+digest before rollback is declared complete. No data migration or persistent
+runner state exists; test results are disposable evidence and are not modified
+by rollback. If the prior digest is unavailable, rollback is blocked and MUST
+escalate rather than substitute a tag or partial downgrade.
+
+## PW-I01 Verification Contract
+
+`tests/test_playwright_bootstrap.py` and generated CI MUST make every PW-I01
+normative requirement observable. At minimum they MUST verify:
+
+1. exact package, engine, script, project, discovery, output, retry, and
+   Chromium-sandbox values;
+2. lockfile version, exact root dependency, allowed `resolved` URL host,
+   integrity presence, and validator fail-closed behavior for each forbidden
+   URL/integrity case;
+3. exact image/tag/digest/platform/version assertions and exact dependency/test
+   phase Docker argument sets;
+4. read-only source/root/dependency boundaries, writable tmpfs/results
+   boundaries, private shared memory, dropped capabilities,
+   no-new-privileges, network modes, environment allowlist, and every forbidden
+   mount/host namespace;
+5. non-root UID/GID rejection and matching result ownership contract;
+6. identical local/CI Make entry points, raw child-exit preservation, and
+   container/volume cleanup on success, command failure, and signal;
+7. a successful PW-I01 platform target using only the non-browser bootstrap
+   spec, with no global Node/npm/Playwright/browser prerequisite.
+
+Static tests may use a fake Docker executable to inspect arguments and lifecycle
+without weakening the required real-container `make test-playwright-platform`
+run. A requirement that cannot be asserted by these observable files, commands,
+or lifecycle outcomes is an architecture defect and MUST be escalated instead
+of implemented by convention.
+
+Normative statements outside PW-I01 are change-control gates. Their review
+package MUST prove the exact source SHA, changed-file inventory, required
+version-coupled file set, command outputs, CI runs, and reviewer verdict. No
+normative requirement in this decision may be accepted only by operator
+assertion or undocumented convention.
+
+## Deferred Decisions And Implementation Freedom
+
+PW-I01 does not decide service networking, secret names, evidence formats,
+final `0/1/2` mapping, retries, reporters, traces, screenshots, authentication,
+service selectors, or secondary browsers. Their later tickets MUST use the
+explicit seams above or amend this decision through independent review before
+changing an image, package, path, script, discovery rule, mount, privilege,
+environment, network, shared-memory, output, or lifecycle contract.
+
+The implementation freedom intentionally left to PW-I01 is limited to shell
+mechanics that are not externally observable: local variable names, equivalent
+array construction, diagnostic wording, and trap implementation. This is not
+permission to invent another architecture contract.
+
